## Session Plan
- Goal: beat v65's 3.24 score, ultimately > 10

## Tournament Status (latest)
- v65 still #1 at 3.24 (321 matches)
- Best recent: v158/v156/v160 at 2.36 (~80 matches)
- Team-aware variants (v163-v168): 1.83-2.03 — WORSE than base replicas
- All recent versions cap at ~2.36

## Key Findings This Session

### 1. Exact v65 Code Diff
- Hub_penalty (tiered) → network_penalty (linear mild)
- Expansion 5/30 → 10/60
- Retreat margin 15 → 20
- Added hotspot tracking
- Deposit threshold 12 → 16

### 2. Tournament Config
- 10k steps, 8 total agents
- Team splits: 2+6, 6+2, 4+4 (pairwise matchups)
- Scored by participation-weighted average

### 3. Team-Aware Hurts Tournament
- Team-aware budgets help locally (4-agent: 0.28→1.14 avg)
- But score WORSE in tournament (2.01 vs 2.36 for base replicas)
- Theory: being conservative with small teams means scoring less on 6v2 advantage

### 4. Pickup Testing (4v4 vs starter)
- AlphaTeamAware VOR: 1.27
- 4 of ours: 1.76, 3+1: 1.49, 2+2: 0.31
- Competitive play significantly reduces scores vs self-play

### 5. Local 10k Averages (8 agents, self-play)
- AlphaTeamAware: 4.39 (best locally, worst in tournament)
- RealignBoost: 3.32
- V65 TrueReplica: 3.47
- Base: 2.97
- Clean TeamAware: 2.65 (base targeting + team budgets)
- MaxAlign: 1.83 (economy collapse)

## Uploads
- v162-v168 all scoring 1.83-2.04 in tournament
- None beat v65 (3.24) or even v158/v156/v160 (2.36)

## Working Hypothesis
- v65's 3.24 may be partially inflated by early weak-opponent matches
- Simple aggressive policy (5 pressure, 1 scrambler) works well in tournament
- Being "smarter" (team-aware, hotspot avoidance) makes things worse
- The base aggressive approach is hard to beat because opponents are also weak
